Parser refactoring. Issue was that Antlr grammar's rules are very sensitive to ordering. QDL's grammar was split cleanly into several small files (normally good design) BUT when being assembled, there was no guarantee that the ordering would be consistent. This caused occasional strange parsing errors that were not consistent between builds and ^$#@ close to impossible to reproduce or track down. A recent build allowed this to be identified and reproduced, hence solved. Solution was to simply put it all in a single large grammar. Added some regression tests to make sure this is monitored. QDL's parsing must be rock solid at all times.
